17:47.467 --> 17:48.501
GLAMOROUS.

17:48.535 --> 17:50.737
- DOES THE TRICK.
- I'M SURE.

17:54.541 --> 17:55.675
YOU KNOW, IF--

17:55.708 --> 17:57.577
IF YOU EVER FEEL LIKE
SELLING, I'M A--

17:57.610 --> 18:00.480
I'M A REALTOR NOW.

18:00.513 --> 18:02.382
- HE'S NOT HERE.

18:02.415 --> 18:03.850
- I KNOW.

18:03.883 --> 18:05.485
THAT'S WHY I CAME.

18:05.518 --> 18:07.520
TO ASK YOU A FAVOR.

18:07.554 --> 18:09.356
- I ALREADY DID YOU ONE.

18:09.389 --> 18:12.425
- YEAH, BUT, UH...

18:12.459 --> 18:15.895
THIS ONE'S FOR HIM.

18:15.928 --> 18:18.565
I WANT YOU TO TAKE HIM.

18:18.598 --> 18:19.699
- EXCUSE ME?

18:19.732 --> 18:22.369
- I WANT YOU TO TAKE
MY SON.

18:26.506 --> 18:28.141
- MRS. TAYLOR...
- JENNIFER.

18:28.175 --> 18:30.277
- WHATEVER.

18:30.310 --> 18:32.379
WHAT THE FUCK ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

18:32.412 --> 18:34.814
- HE, UM...

18:34.847 --> 18:37.217
WON'T LET ANYONE TOUCH HIM,
WON'T...

18:37.250 --> 18:39.619
LET ANYONE NEAR HIM.

18:39.652 --> 18:41.221
HE SHOWS PRACTICALLY
NO EMOTION

18:41.254 --> 18:43.656
EXCEPT WHEN HE'S IN ONE OF HIS
RAGES, OR HE...

18:43.690 --> 18:45.492
WAKES UP SCREAMING
FROM A NIGHTMARE.

18:45.525 --> 18:46.826
BUT THAT'S NOT EVEN
THE WORST PART.

18:46.859 --> 18:48.828
THE WORST PART IS, UM...

18:48.861 --> 18:53.200
STANDING THERE...
HELPLESS.

18:53.233 --> 18:57.136
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT THAT FEELS LIKE?

18:58.871 --> 19:01.808
- WHAT WOULD YOU
LIKE ME TO DO?

19:01.841 --> 19:05.778
- TOUCH HIM.

19:05.812 --> 19:07.614
HELP HIM BE TOUCHED.

19:09.682 --> 19:11.551
- YOU WANT ME TO FUCK HIM?

19:13.653 --> 19:17.790
- WELL, UH...

19:17.824 --> 19:21.794
YOU'RE THE ONE HE TRUSTS.

19:21.828 --> 19:24.331
IF THAT'S WHAT IT TAKES...

19:24.364 --> 19:26.599
- I THOUGHT YOU NEVER
WANTED ME TO SEE HIM AGAIN.

19:26.633 --> 19:28.201
- I DON'T.

19:28.235 --> 19:30.370
BUT, UM...

19:30.403 --> 19:32.239
IF I'M EVER GOING TO...

19:32.272 --> 19:37.610
SEE MY SON EVEN REMOTELY
RESEMBLE THE PERSON HE WAS,

19:37.644 --> 19:39.178
I DON'T HAVE A CHOICE.

19:45.252 --> 19:46.319
- THEN THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO?

19:46.353 --> 19:48.621
NO RECOURSE, NO LAWSUIT,
NO DAMAGES?

19:48.655 --> 19:49.656
- IN TWO WORDS, TEDDY:

19:49.689 --> 19:51.291
YOU'RE SCREWED.

19:51.324 --> 19:52.825
- ACTUALLY, THAT'S THREE
WITH THE CONTRACTION.

19:52.859 --> 19:54.361
- [chuckles]

19:54.394 --> 19:55.728
- OW!
[muttering]

19:55.762 --> 19:57.730
FUCK THIS THING.

19:57.764 --> 19:58.898
THERE'S NO LAW IN THIS STATE

19:58.931 --> 20:01.401
THAT PREVENTS DISCRIMINATION
OF GAYS IN THE WORKPLACE.

20:01.434 --> 20:03.703
WERTSHAFTER CAN DO WHATEVER
THE HELL HE WANTS.

20:03.736 --> 20:05.472
YEAH...
FUCKING SON OF A BITCH.

20:05.505 --> 20:07.407
YOU KNOW, I HAVE A MIND
TO WALK RIGHT IN

20:07.440 --> 20:08.408
TO TELL HIM
EXACTLY HOW I FEEL!

20:08.441 --> 20:09.776
- WHY DON'T YOU?

20:09.809 --> 20:11.278
LOOK HIM STRAIGHT IN THE EYE,
AND TELL HIM

20:11.311 --> 20:12.712
THAT EVEN THOUGH THE LAW
PERMITS IT,

20:12.745 --> 20:14.714
YOU THINK WHAT HE DID IS
UNJUSTIFIED AND UNCONSCIONABLE.

20:14.747 --> 20:18.651
- RIGHT.
I JUST MIGHT DO THAT.

20:18.685 --> 20:19.686
MAYBE.

20:19.719 --> 20:20.987
- [sighs]

20:21.020 --> 20:22.021
- ALL RIGHT,
THANKS FOR THE ADVICE.

20:22.054 --> 20:23.323
AND THE SUCKER.

20:23.356 --> 20:25.792
- BYE.
- BYE.

20:25.825 --> 20:27.394
POOR TED.

20:27.427 --> 20:29.862
- JUST ONE MORE EXAMPLE
OF HAVING NO RIGHTS.

20:29.896 --> 20:30.863
- LIKE GETTING MARRIED.

20:30.897 --> 20:33.466
- YOU--ARE YOU GOING TO START
WITH THAT AGAIN?

20:33.500 --> 20:35.735
- HEY, WILL YOU LET ME
FINISH?

20:35.768 --> 20:38.305
THAT NIGHT WE CAME BACK
FROM MY SISTER'S WEDDING,

20:38.338 --> 20:39.706
I WENT INTO THE GARDEN
AFTER YOU FELL ASLEEP.

20:39.739 --> 20:41.040
- YOU DID?

20:41.073 --> 20:43.476
- MM-HM. I STOOD
AND IMAGINED EXACTLY

20:43.510 --> 20:45.312
HOW I WANTED OUR WEDDING
TO LOOK.

20:45.345 --> 20:46.746
A WHATCHA-CALLIT,
A HOOPA?

20:46.779 --> 20:47.747
- CHUPPAH.

20:47.780 --> 20:49.849
- CHUPPAH
UNDER THE SYCAMORES,

20:49.882 --> 20:52.018
WHITE SATIN RIBBON BOWS
ON THE ARBORS

20:52.051 --> 20:54.754
AND LITTLE TWINKLING LIGHTS
EVERYWHERE, LIKE THE MILKY WAY.

20:54.787 --> 20:55.988
- UH-HUH.

20:56.022 --> 20:57.089
- BUT TODAY,
I WAS OUTSIDE

20:57.123 --> 20:59.959
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT HOW
TO DECORATE FOR GUS'S PARTY,

20:59.992 --> 21:03.463
AND I SAID TO MYSELF,
"PETERSON, WHAT THE HELL

21:03.496 --> 21:05.365
"WERE YOU THINKING?

21:05.398 --> 21:07.500
"I MEAN, YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
20 TOTS HERE ON SATURDAY.

21:07.534 --> 21:08.335
"YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO DEAL WITH

21:08.368 --> 21:11.538
"TANTRUMS AND TEARS
AND THROW-UP.

21:11.571 --> 21:13.673
"MEL'S RIGHT.

21:13.706 --> 21:16.476
THE TIME TO BE ROMANTIC
HAS PASSED."

21:17.810 --> 21:20.747
- WELL...NO.

21:20.780 --> 21:21.714
I DIDN'T MEAN THAT.

21:21.748 --> 21:24.016
- "IT'S A SILLY RITUAL
FOR STRAIGHT PEOPLE.

21:24.050 --> 21:26.386
A BANKRUPT INSTITUTION."

21:26.419 --> 21:29.789
NO. WE HAVE TO BE
PRACTICAL NOW.

21:29.822 --> 21:32.392
SO I APOLOGIZE FOR MAKING
SUCH A BIG DEAL.

21:32.425 --> 21:33.693
AND I PROMISE

21:33.726 --> 21:38.898
TO NEVER,
NEVER MENTION IT AGAIN.

21:38.931 --> 21:42.669
- SHE THOUGHT SHE COULD
KEEP US APART.

21:42.702 --> 21:45.738
[high-pitched] "I DON'T WANT YOU
SEEING MY SON ANYMORE."

21:45.772 --> 21:47.540
WE SHOWED HER.

21:47.574 --> 21:49.609
- WOULD YOU SHUT UP?
- WHAT FOR?

21:49.642 --> 21:51.077
- BECAUSE I SAID SO,
AND BECAUSE YOU SOUND LIKE

21:51.110 --> 21:52.945
AN IMMATURE BRAT.

21:52.979 --> 21:55.782
- MAYBE I AM.

21:55.815 --> 21:59.786
- THEN YOU CAN GET YOUR ASS OUT
AND WALK HOME.

21:59.819 --> 22:03.523
RIGHT NOW.

22:03.556 --> 22:06.459
- WHAT IS THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

22:06.493 --> 22:07.960
- SHE WAS TRYING TO DO
THE RIGHT THING.

22:07.994 --> 22:09.128
YOU DON'T KNOW
HOW LUCKY YOU ARE

22:09.161 --> 22:11.831
TO HAVE A MOTHER
LIKE THAT.

22:11.864 --> 22:13.933
- NOW I GET TO STAY WITH YOU.

22:13.966 --> 22:15.735
YEE-HAW!

22:15.768 --> 22:19.706
- JUST UNTIL YOU GET BETTER.

22:19.739 --> 22:21.874
- THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH ME.

22:21.908 --> 22:25.011
EXCEPT FOR MY...
GIMP HAND.

22:25.044 --> 22:27.747
FUCKING HOBBS.

22:27.780 --> 22:32.552
- JUST DON'T THINK ABOUT IT,
ALL RIGHT?

22:32.585 --> 22:34.053
- HOW COME YOU'RE DOING THIS?

22:34.086 --> 22:36.055
- WHAT, DRIVING
WITH NO HANDS?

22:36.088 --> 22:38.391
- NO, WHY ARE YOU
LETTING ME STAY WITH YOU?

22:38.425 --> 22:42.895
- WHY DO YOU CARE?
IT'S WHAT YOU WANT, ISN'T IT?

22:42.929 --> 22:44.597
- I KNOW WHY.

22:44.631 --> 22:47.066
IT'S BECAUSE
YOU LOVE ME MADLY,

22:47.099 --> 22:50.002
PASSIONATELY, DEEPLY...

22:50.036 --> 22:52.104
JUST LIKE
I ALWAYS SUSPECTED.

22:52.138 --> 22:54.741
- GET THE REST OF THAT
STUFF OFF THE TRUCK.

22:54.774 --> 22:57.109
- THIS IS A PRETTY
FANCY PLACE.

22:57.143 --> 22:58.978
- WELL, FOR WHAT THEY'RE
PAYING US, IT'D HAVE TO BE.

22:59.011 --> 23:01.080
[chuckles]

23:01.113 --> 23:02.649
- I'VE NEVER
BEEN A WAITER.

23:02.682 --> 23:04.116
HOPE I CAN DO IT.

23:04.150 --> 23:07.587
- HONEY...THIS IS
YOUR FAMILY BUSINESS.

23:07.620 --> 23:09.155
IT'S IN YOUR BLOOD.

23:09.188 --> 23:11.591
NOW, YOU MAKE YOUR MOTHER
PROUD.

23:11.624 --> 23:13.059
- ARE YOU TWO
THE WAITERS?

23:13.092 --> 23:15.462
- UH, YES, SIR.

23:15.495 --> 23:16.829
- OHH.

23:16.863 --> 23:18.130
WELL, WHY AREN'T YOU DRESSED?

23:18.164 --> 23:19.732
- UM, THEY SAID YOU'D
GIVE US OUR UNIFORMS

23:19.766 --> 23:20.967
WHEN WE GOT HERE.

23:21.000 --> 23:23.069
- OH, THE OUTFITS.
WHERE ARE THEIR OUTFITS?

23:23.102 --> 23:24.136
QUICKLY.
- RIGHT HERE.

23:24.170 --> 23:26.973
- QUICKLY.

23:27.006 --> 23:28.808
HURRY UP
AND PUT THESE ON.

23:30.810 --> 23:32.612
- IS EVERYTHING
OFF THE TRUCK?

23:32.645 --> 23:34.180
- WHERE'S THE REST OF THE TUX?

23:34.213 --> 23:35.815
- UGH.

23:35.848 --> 23:37.149
- UM, E-EXCUSE ME,
I-I THINK THERE'S BEEN A--

23:37.183 --> 23:39.085
A MISTAKE.

23:41.153 --> 23:42.154
[chatter and laughter]

23:42.188 --> 23:43.856
- WHATEVER HAPPENED TO HER?

23:43.890 --> 23:44.991
[laughter]

23:45.024 --> 23:45.992
- OH. SHH, SHH. SHH.

23:46.025 --> 23:47.560
- DESSERT'S A LITTLE EARLY.

23:47.594 --> 23:48.595
[laughter]

23:48.628 --> 23:51.831
- OOH...APPETIZERS.

23:51.864 --> 23:54.166
- UH, WH-WHITE WINE,
OR--OR RED?

23:54.200 --> 23:55.201
- UH, WHITE.

23:55.234 --> 23:57.003
- VERY GOOD, SIR.

23:59.271 --> 24:01.608
[men chuckling lewdly]

24:01.641 --> 24:02.742
- AND RED.

24:02.775 --> 24:04.944
- SOME GUYS HAVE
ALL THE LUCK.

24:04.977 --> 24:07.547
[all chuckling]
- HE'S GONNA WAIT FOR THE MEAT.

24:07.580 --> 24:09.716
[indistinct chatter]

24:09.749 --> 24:10.883
- SHRIMP BALLS?

24:10.917 --> 24:13.185
- I WOULDN'T SAY THAT.

24:13.219 --> 24:14.887
OOH-OOH-HOO!

24:14.921 --> 24:17.857
[men laughing]

24:19.892 --> 24:21.961
- KEEP YOUR HANDS OFF
THE TENDERLOIN.

24:21.994 --> 24:22.962
all: OOH...

24:22.995 --> 24:24.931
- WHOO, PRECIOUS.

24:37.043 --> 24:39.245
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING
ALL THE WAY OVER THERE?

24:42.649 --> 24:44.884
- COME CLOSER.

24:49.321 --> 24:51.991
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE OFF SOME
OF THE CLOTHES?

24:52.024 --> 24:54.226
YOU MIGHT GET OVERHEATED.

25:20.052 --> 25:21.253
ROLL OVER.

25:53.753 --> 25:56.222
- NO, DON'T.
DON'T.

25:56.255 --> 25:58.825
[panting]

26:02.028 --> 26:03.896
I CAN'T.

26:20.146 --> 26:22.214
- IT'S OKAY.

26:22.248 --> 26:24.216
- IT'S NOT OKAY.

26:34.727 --> 26:36.863
- YOU KNOW, FOR SOMEONE
WHO HAS ENOUGH DISORDERS

26:36.896 --> 26:38.965
TO MERIT YOUR OWN
CLASSIFICATION

26:38.998 --> 26:41.668
IN THE DIAGNOSTIC
AND STATISTICAL MANUAL,

26:41.701 --> 26:44.370
YOU ARE ONE OF THE MOST
WELL ADJUSTED

26:44.403 --> 26:48.107
AND HIGH FUNCTIONING
BASTARDS I KNOW.

26:48.140 --> 26:50.843
- THANKS.
