26:50.877 --> 26:54.280
- A SERIES OF HOPELESS
ADDICTIONS, FOR ONE.

26:54.313 --> 26:58.885
AND NEVER SEEING A SHRINK,
FOR ANOTHER.

27:00.953 --> 27:03.255
- YOU'RE SEEING ONE NOW.

27:03.289 --> 27:05.858
SO, UH, YOU TRIED
TO HOLD HIM,

27:05.892 --> 27:06.959
TO HAVE SEX WITH HIM,

27:06.993 --> 27:10.229
BUT HE WOULDN'T LET YOU
TOUCH HIM?

27:10.262 --> 27:13.900
THAT MUST BE A FIRST
FOR YOU.

27:13.933 --> 27:15.768
HOWEVER,
IT'S UNDERSTANDABLE.

27:15.802 --> 27:17.670
SOMETHING LIKE THAT
HAPPENS,

27:17.704 --> 27:20.406
NATURALLY HE'S GOING TO BE
AFRAID TO LET ANYONE TOUCH HIM.

27:20.439 --> 27:22.842
EVEN YOU.
- BUT HE'LL GET OVER IT, RIGHT?

27:22.875 --> 27:26.145
THAT DEPENDS.
IT'S LIKE A--A FAIRY TALE.

27:26.178 --> 27:28.347
RAPUNZEL
TRAPPED IN THE TOWER,

27:28.380 --> 27:30.116
HANSEL AND GRETEL
CAGED BY THE WITCH.

27:30.149 --> 27:31.784
ONLY IN THIS CASE,

27:31.818 --> 27:35.722
IT'S JUSTIN'S MEMORY
THAT'S BEEN LOCKED UP.

27:35.755 --> 27:39.158
AND IT'S--IT'S UP TO YOU
TO RELEASE IT,

27:39.191 --> 27:41.327
HANDSOME PRINCE.

27:41.360 --> 27:44.163
- [sighs]
AND...

27:44.196 --> 27:45.765
HOW THE FUCK
DO I DO THAT?

27:45.798 --> 27:47.767
- TRIGGER HIS MEMORY.

27:47.800 --> 27:51.003
GET HIM TO FEEL THE PAIN.

27:51.037 --> 27:52.071
- ARE YOU SHITTING ME?

27:52.104 --> 27:55.975
NO. UNTIL HE CAN PROCESS IT
AND MOVE BEYOND IT,

27:56.008 --> 27:59.912
HE'S ALWAYS GOING TO FEEL
ISOLATED, UNHAPPY, ALONE.

27:59.946 --> 28:03.315
HE'S NOT JUST THE WALKING
WOUNDED.

28:03.349 --> 28:05.117
THE WALKING DEAD.

28:08.287 --> 28:10.389
- AHH.

28:10.422 --> 28:12.324
YOU'RE VERY ELOQUENT
WHEN I'M DRUNK.

28:12.358 --> 28:16.028
- [snorts]

28:16.062 --> 28:17.764
I'M AFRAID OUR TIME'S UP.

28:21.367 --> 28:25.204
- SO HOW MUCH DO I OWE YOU?

28:25.237 --> 28:28.274
- I'LL TAKE IT OUT
IN TRADE...

28:29.508 --> 28:31.811
NEXT TIME I SEE YOU
IN THE BATHS.

28:31.844 --> 28:33.712
- HEH.

28:38.250 --> 28:40.853
- IT WAS AWFUL.

28:40.887 --> 28:42.755
ALL THESE DIRTY-MINDED
OLD MEN

28:42.789 --> 28:44.423
STARING AT ME
AND PINCHING MY ASS.

28:44.456 --> 28:46.358
- IT WAS FABULOUS. ALL THESE
DIRTY-MINDED OLD MEN

28:46.392 --> 28:48.494
STARING AT ME,
PINCHING MY ASS.

28:48.527 --> 28:50.029
- WELCOME TO
POINT-COUNTERPOINT.

28:50.062 --> 28:52.131
- BESIDES, WHAT ARE A FEW
BRUISE MARKS?

28:52.164 --> 28:54.233
NOW, DOESN'T THAT FEEL
BETTER?

28:54.266 --> 28:56.836
WE EACH MADE $500.

28:56.869 --> 28:58.370
- HOW MUCH IS THAT
AFTER TAXES?

28:58.404 --> 28:59.338
- WHAT ARE YOU
ASKING ME FOR?

28:59.371 --> 29:01.974
- YOU'RE AN ACCOUNTANT.
- WAS AN ACCOUNTANT.

29:02.008 --> 29:04.210
- WELL, IT'S CLEAR TO ME
WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO.

29:04.243 --> 29:07.113
- HOW TO OPEN A MILK CARTON
ISN'T CLEAR TO YOU.

29:07.146 --> 29:10.316
NEVERTHELESS, I CAN'T WAIT
TO HEAR YOUR THOUGHTS.

29:10.349 --> 29:12.151
- SUE HIM.

29:12.184 --> 29:14.386
KICK HIS HOMOPHOBIC ASS...

29:14.420 --> 29:16.088
- OW!
- OH.

29:16.122 --> 29:18.925
SORRY, SWEETIE. TO COURT.
AND SUE HIM FOR 10 MIL.

29:18.958 --> 29:20.893
NO, MAKE IT 20.
OKAY, THERE.

29:20.927 --> 29:23.429
[chuckles]
MY TURN.

29:23.462 --> 29:25.798
- THAT'S BRILLIANT,
ONLY, MELANIE TOLD ME

29:25.832 --> 29:27.133
THERE'S NO LAWS
IN THIS STATE

29:27.166 --> 29:29.535
COVERING DISCRIMINATION
BASED ON SEXUAL ORIENTATION.

29:29.568 --> 29:31.370
- SCRATCH THAT.

29:31.403 --> 29:33.339
- NO, JUST RUB.

29:35.207 --> 29:37.109
- I'M GOING TO TALK
TO WERTSHAFTER.

29:37.143 --> 29:38.978
CONFRONT HIM LIKE A MAN.
TELL HIM, "LOOK,

29:39.011 --> 29:41.147
"I'VE BEEN A LOYAL AND DEVOTED
EMPLOYEE HERE FOR NINE YEARS.

29:41.180 --> 29:42.414
"YOU'VE GOT NO RIGHT
TO TREAT ME LIKE THIS

29:42.448 --> 29:44.550
JUST BECAUSE I'M GAY."

29:44.583 --> 29:46.819
THEN I'M GOING TO GROVEL.

29:46.853 --> 29:48.020
- SOUNDS LIKE A PLAN.

29:48.054 --> 29:51.023
- WHAT KIND OF PATHETIC
PUSSY BOYS ARE YOU?

29:51.057 --> 29:52.925
WHERE'S YOUR PRIDE?
WHERE'S YOUR SELF-RESPECT?

29:52.959 --> 29:54.026
WHERE'S YOUR DIGNITY?

29:54.060 --> 29:56.562
[phone rings]

29:56.595 --> 29:57.563
HELLO?

29:57.596 --> 30:00.599
YES, THIS IS HE.

30:00.632 --> 30:02.902
WHAT? YES, I-I BELIEVE
I WOULD BE AVAILABLE.

30:02.935 --> 30:04.170
MM-HMM.

30:04.203 --> 30:07.039
MM-HMM.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

30:08.340 --> 30:09.942
A WEALTHY CLIENT WOULD LIKE
AN ATTRACTIVE DOMESTIC

30:09.976 --> 30:11.543
TO POLISH HIS SILVER.

30:11.577 --> 30:12.644
- I HOPE YOUR ASS HOLDS UP.

30:12.678 --> 30:15.547
- HMM. 100 BUCKS AN HOUR
BUYS AN AWFUL LOT OF LOTION.

30:15.581 --> 30:17.984
ALL RIGHT, BOYS.
I'M OFF TO BUFF IN THE BUFF!

30:18.017 --> 30:19.518
- SO MUCH FOR DIGNITY.

30:25.191 --> 30:27.193
- * I KNOW THERE'S
A MAGIC KEY *

30:27.226 --> 30:29.228
*

30:29.261 --> 30:30.596
* GONNA FIND IT SOON,
YOU'LL SEE *

30:30.629 --> 30:34.133
- WELL...WE WERE DANCING.

30:34.166 --> 30:37.136
AND, UM, I THINK THEY WERE
PLAYING THIS.

30:37.169 --> 30:38.537
ANYWAYS, THAT'S WHEN
BRIAN CAME IN,

30:38.570 --> 30:41.207
AND HE HAD ON...A TUX.

30:41.240 --> 30:44.310
AND A WHITE SILK SCARF.

30:44.343 --> 30:47.013
*

30:47.046 --> 30:50.282
- I THINK I REMEMBER THAT.

30:50.316 --> 30:52.618
I'M NOT SURE.

30:52.651 --> 30:56.122
- WELL, UM...
HE LOOKED AWESOME!

30:56.155 --> 31:00.459
AND HE SAID TO ME...

31:00.492 --> 31:03.495
- YOU LOOK HOT, DAPHNE.
I'D FUCK YOU.

31:03.529 --> 31:05.331
[giggles]

31:05.364 --> 31:08.367
AND THEN HE ASKED
IF HE COULD BORROW YOU

31:08.400 --> 31:10.336
TO DANCE,
AND HE TOOK YOUR HAND,

31:10.369 --> 31:13.172
AND, UH, LED YOU
TO THE DANCE FLOOR.

31:15.707 --> 31:18.377
THEY WERE PLAYING THIS.

31:18.410 --> 31:21.147
- CLOSE YOUR EYES.

31:21.180 --> 31:22.681
MAYBE, UH...

31:22.714 --> 31:24.283
YOU'LL REMEMBER SOMETHING.

31:24.316 --> 31:27.519
- * WHEN I HEAR EVERYBODY SAY

31:27.553 --> 31:32.191
* THAT OLD CLICHE
ABOUT A FISH IN THE SEA *

31:32.224 --> 31:33.993
* I JUST LAUGH

31:34.026 --> 31:35.694
* 'CAUSE THEY GOT NO CLUE

31:35.727 --> 31:40.332
* HOW I FEEL FOR YOU,
YOU'RE THE ONE FOR ME *

31:40.366 --> 31:42.401
* AND WHEN YOU'RE DOWN

31:42.434 --> 31:45.037
* WHAT LOVE'S ABOUT,
BABY, YOU KNOW IT'S TRUE *

31:45.071 --> 31:47.506
- [sighs]
- WELL?

31:47.539 --> 31:51.443
- WE REALLY DANCED
TO THIS CORNY OLD SONG?

31:51.477 --> 31:54.013
- [chuckles]
WELL...

31:54.046 --> 32:00.719
MY--I'D PREFER TO THINK OF IT
AS "RIDICULOUSLY ROMANTIC."

32:00.752 --> 32:03.389
- YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN IT.

32:03.422 --> 32:06.525
YOU AND BRIAN HAD
THE ENTIRE FLOOR TO YOURSELVES.

32:06.558 --> 32:08.427
- * OH, I COULD NEVER GO

32:08.460 --> 32:10.462
- WE DID SOME, UM...

32:10.496 --> 32:11.630
PRETTY FANCY MOVES.

32:11.663 --> 32:13.099
- * YOU KNOW IT TOO

32:13.132 --> 32:15.167
- MOUTHS WERE DROPPING.

32:15.201 --> 32:16.568
IT WAS SO COOL,
AND THEN,

32:16.602 --> 32:18.370
WHEN YOU GUYS KISSED...

32:18.404 --> 32:20.372
IT WAS SO HOT.

32:20.406 --> 32:23.575
- YOU KISSED ME?

32:23.609 --> 32:25.744
IN FRONT OF EVERYBODY?

32:25.777 --> 32:29.181
- YEAH.

32:29.215 --> 32:31.117
YOU SHOULD'VE BEEN THERE.

32:31.150 --> 32:33.719
- * I'M THE ONLY ONE
FOR YOU *

32:33.752 --> 32:35.521
* THAT YOU'RE MINE

32:35.554 --> 32:40.259
* AND I'M THE ONLY ONE
FOR YOU *

32:40.292 --> 32:43.229
- SO, FIRST DAY BACK.
HOW'D YOU FEEL?

32:43.262 --> 32:46.465
- HEH, LIKE I NEVER LEFT.
- I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

32:46.498 --> 32:48.767
WORKING AT THE BIG Q KIND OF
SPOILS YOU FOR ANYTHING ELSE.

32:48.800 --> 32:51.270
- [chuckles] YEAH.
- THERE YOU ARE, NOVOTNY.

32:51.303 --> 32:52.738
STELLA JUST CALLED IN SICK.

32:52.771 --> 32:54.773
I NEED YOU TO STAY
TILL MIDNIGHT.

32:54.806 --> 32:57.343
- BUT I JUST FINISHED
A 10-HOUR SHIFT.

32:57.376 --> 32:59.578
- ARE YOU SAYING
YOU HAVE A PROBLEM?

32:59.611 --> 33:01.447
BECAUSE I'D HATE TO THINK
I HIRED AN ASSISTANT MANAGER

33:01.480 --> 33:05.017
WHO'S REFUSING
TO DO THE JOB.

33:05.051 --> 33:07.219
- SURE, I'LL STAY.
HAPPY TO.

33:07.253 --> 33:08.487
- GOOD.

33:08.520 --> 33:10.689
TAKE OFF YOUR COAT,
MAKE YOURSELF AT HOME,

33:10.722 --> 33:13.125
AND START RETAGGING THESE.

33:13.159 --> 33:14.593
SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

33:14.626 --> 33:17.629
OH. AND, UH...

33:17.663 --> 33:19.065
WELCOME BACK.

33:25.404 --> 33:27.639
- LOOK, I CAN CALL MY
BOYFRIEND AND CANCEL DINNER.

33:27.673 --> 33:30.276
UH, HE NEEDS TO LOSE
A FEW POUNDS ANYWAY.

33:30.309 --> 33:32.111
- NO, NO, NO, NO.
YOU GO ON, TRACE.

33:32.144 --> 33:35.514
THERE'S NO REASON EVERYONE'S
NIGHT SHOULD BE RUINED.

33:35.547 --> 33:37.483
- [sighs]
OKAY.

33:39.818 --> 33:42.754
- [on P.A.]
ATTENTION, BIG Q SHOPPERS,

33:42.788 --> 33:46.158
THE STORE WILL BE CLOSING
IN 15 MINUTES.

34:18.157 --> 34:22.428
- [sighs]

34:22.461 --> 34:27.799
- YOU WALKED DOWN WITH ME
BACK TO THE JEEP.

34:27.833 --> 34:31.103
AND WE WERE, UH...
WE WERE GOOFING...

34:31.137 --> 34:33.805
SINGING,
AND WE WERE DANCING...

34:33.839 --> 34:35.274
[laughter]

34:35.307 --> 34:37.709
I KISSED YOU.
YOU SAID, "LATER."

34:37.743 --> 34:40.312
- LATER.

34:40.346 --> 34:42.548
- AND THEN YOU TURNED AROUND,
AND, UM...

34:42.581 --> 34:44.183
SMILED.

34:44.216 --> 34:45.817
[chuckles]

34:45.851 --> 34:48.754
- HEH, THEN I KNEW WHY DEBBIE
CALLS YOU SUNSHINE.

34:54.860 --> 34:57.163
- AND THEN I WENT BACK
TO THE JEEP AND AS I...

34:57.196 --> 34:59.198
SAW HIM IN THE MIRROR COMING
AFTER YOU...

34:59.231 --> 35:00.866
- JUSTIN!

35:00.899 --> 35:02.701
[thud]

35:02.734 --> 35:04.870
[running footsteps]

35:04.903 --> 35:06.172
[bat clatters to ground]

35:06.205 --> 35:09.541
CHRIST!

35:09.575 --> 35:13.645
DON'T YOU...
REMEMBER ANYTHING?

35:15.481 --> 35:17.449
- [sighs]

35:19.418 --> 35:20.886
- [sighs]

35:42.541 --> 35:45.411
- I WISH I COULD REMEMBER.

35:50.716 --> 35:52.784
- I WISH I COULD FORGET.

36:05.664 --> 36:08.234
- SCHMIDT. WHAT ARE YOU
STILL DOING HERE?

36:08.267 --> 36:11.570
- I, UH, CAME BY TO PICK UP
MY MR. COFFEE, AND...

36:11.603 --> 36:15.274
TO SPEAK WITH YOU, SIR,
IF I MAY.

36:16.575 --> 36:17.943
[clears throat]
MR. WERTSHAFTER,

36:17.976 --> 36:21.247
AS A LOYAL AND DEVOTED
EMPLOYEE HERE OF NINE YEARS...

36:21.280 --> 36:24.783
- 8 YEARS,
11 MONTHS, 6 DAYS.

36:24.816 --> 36:27.719
- [chuckles]

36:27.753 --> 36:30.222
YOU ALWAYS WERE
PRECISE, SIR.

36:30.256 --> 36:32.724
RIGHT DOWN TO THE DIGIT.

36:32.758 --> 36:34.826
THAT'S WHY IT SAYS
WERTSHAFTER ON THE DOOR,

36:34.860 --> 36:36.828
I GUESS...
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW...

36:36.862 --> 36:37.896
[nervous chuckle]

36:41.600 --> 36:44.670
I JUST--I WANT--
I WANT YOU TO KNOW HOW...

36:44.703 --> 36:47.839
UNREASONABLE AND UNFAIR
I THINK IT IS

36:47.873 --> 36:50.842
THAT YOU DISMISSED ME OVER
SUCH A MINOR INFRACTION.

36:50.876 --> 36:51.777
I'M SURE IF IT HAD BEEN
ONE OF THE OTHERS,

36:51.810 --> 36:53.445
YOU WOULD'VE JUST
LOOKED THE OTHER WAY.

36:53.479 --> 36:55.847
THE ONLY DIFFERENCE
IS BECAUSE I'M--I'M--

36:55.881 --> 36:57.416
- A HOMOSEXUAL.

36:57.449 --> 36:58.984
- PRECISELY.

36:59.017 --> 37:00.952
- YOU GAYS,

37:00.986 --> 37:03.822
EVERY TIME SOMETHING HAPPENS,
YOU THINK IT'S DISCRIMINATION.

37:03.855 --> 37:05.657
WELL, THIS ISN'T ABOUT
DISCRIMINATION.

37:05.691 --> 37:07.893
THIS IS ABOUT
COMPANY POLICY:

37:07.926 --> 37:09.361
"ANYONE FOUND
USING THE INTERNET

37:09.395 --> 37:11.563
"FOR REASONS OTHER
THAN BUSINESS PURPOSES

37:11.597 --> 37:14.700
WILL BE DISMISSED
FORTHWITH."

37:14.733 --> 37:15.867
YOU'RE LUCKY
I DIDN'T CHARGE YOU

37:15.901 --> 37:19.037
FOR THE TIME YOU SPENT
ONLINE.

37:19.070 --> 37:22.274
- YES, SIR.
THANK YOU, SIR.

37:23.709 --> 37:26.345
- SCHMIDT.
- YES, SIR?

37:26.378 --> 37:28.314
- ONE MORE THING.

37:28.347 --> 37:29.981
ARE YOU HAPPY
BEING AN ACCOUNTANT?

37:30.015 --> 37:32.484
- HAPPY?
- DOES BALANCING THE BOOKS

37:32.518 --> 37:34.653
MAKE YOUR HEART
BEAT FASTER?

37:40.091 --> 37:42.461
- NO, SIR.
NOT REALLY.

37:42.494 --> 37:44.830
- THEN I'M DOING YOU
A FAVOR.

37:44.863 --> 37:46.632
NEXT TIME,
FIND YOURSELF SOMETHING

37:46.665 --> 37:47.966
YOU HAVE A PASSION FOR.

37:47.999 --> 37:52.270
OTHERWISE, YOU'RE JUST
JERKING YOURSELF OFF.

38:02.614 --> 38:05.451
[chatter and cheers]

38:07.586 --> 38:09.688
- ISN'T THAT GORGEOUS?

38:11.089 --> 38:12.758
- LOOKY HERE.

38:12.791 --> 38:14.760
MAKE A WISH, SWEETHEART!

38:14.793 --> 38:16.462
- I WANT A NEW JOB.
I WANT A NEW JOB.

38:16.495 --> 38:17.863
- NOT YOU.

38:17.896 --> 38:20.366
- HE'S TOO YOUNG.
AND I REALLY NEED IT.

38:20.399 --> 38:22.368
- ONE, TWO, THREE.

38:22.401 --> 38:23.535
[big inhale]

38:23.569 --> 38:25.036
[blowing]

38:25.070 --> 38:26.905
[cheers and applause]

38:26.938 --> 38:30.642
- LET'S HAVE SOME CAKE!

38:30.676 --> 38:32.077
- YOU KNOW, I WOULD JUST
LIKE TO SAY

38:32.110 --> 38:34.480
WHAT A THRILL IT IS
FOR LINDSAY AND ME

38:34.513 --> 38:36.348
TO BE CELEBRATING OUR
BEAUTIFUL SON'S

38:36.382 --> 38:37.683
VERY FIRST BIRTHDAY,

38:37.716 --> 38:39.685
AND HOW HAPPY WE ARE.

38:39.718 --> 38:42.454
HOW VERY HAPPY THAT YOU'RE
ALL HERE TO SHARE IT WITH US.

38:42.488 --> 38:43.555
- THANKS FOR HAVING US.

38:43.589 --> 38:45.090
- WILL YOU CUT THE SCHMALTZ
SO I CAN CUT THE CAKE?

38:45.123 --> 38:46.625
- THAT'S TELLING 'EM, SIS.

38:46.658 --> 38:48.660
- OKAY, GRAB A PLATE
BEFORE THE ICE CREAM MELTS.

38:48.694 --> 38:50.396
COME ON.

38:50.429 --> 38:52.464
- HI.
- I WANT SOME CAKE.

38:52.498 --> 38:55.133
- THANK YOU.

38:55.166 --> 38:57.035
[indistinct chatter]

38:57.068 --> 38:58.336
- [chuckles]

38:59.871 --> 39:01.339
- MMM.

39:02.941 --> 39:04.075
- YES, HONEY?

39:04.109 --> 39:05.877
- ARE YOU AND HER MARRIED?

39:05.911 --> 39:09.581
- UM...

39:09.615 --> 39:11.550
- NO, SWEETIE, WE'RE NOT.

39:11.583 --> 39:13.519
- HOW COME?

39:13.552 --> 39:14.753
- ASK YOUR MOMMY AND DADDY

39:14.786 --> 39:16.588
TO EXPLAIN IT TO YOU
IN ABOUT...

39:16.622 --> 39:18.089
OH, 20 YEARS.

39:19.491 --> 39:21.827
[giggles]

39:32.638 --> 39:35.140
- WANT SOME?

39:35.173 --> 39:36.875
- YOU KNOW, WHITE FLOUR
AND WHITE SUGAR

39:36.908 --> 39:39.845
ARE ABOUT THE WORST THING
YOU CAN PUT IN YOUR BODY.

39:39.878 --> 39:40.846
- UH-HUH.

39:48.587 --> 39:52.624
30 YEARS AGO...

39:52.658 --> 39:55.527
WE HAD YOUR FIRST BIRTHDAY
PARTY.

39:55.561 --> 40:00.198
IN THE BACKYARD...WITH THE KIDS
AND THE CAKE...

40:00.231 --> 40:02.601
AND THE SWING SET.
HUH.

40:02.634 --> 40:06.505
I STILL DON'T KNOW
WHAT A GRATCHET IS.

40:06.538 --> 40:09.741
SOME THINGS NEVER CHANGE,
HUH?

40:16.882 --> 40:19.718
- YOU'RE WRONG, MA.

40:19.751 --> 40:21.820
THINGS CHANGE A LOT.

40:21.853 --> 40:23.054
IF YOU DON'T
CHANGE WITH THEM,

40:23.088 --> 40:26.658
YOU GET LEFT BEHIND.

40:26.692 --> 40:28.927
LOOK AT ME, I'M--
I'M RIGHT BACK

40:28.960 --> 40:31.530
IN THE SAME PLACE
I WAS BEFORE,

40:31.563 --> 40:34.065
AND EVERYBODY ELSE
HAS MOVED ON.

40:37.068 --> 40:39.505
I FEEL LOST, MA.

40:41.940 --> 40:44.643
- OH, BABY.

40:44.676 --> 40:47.913
YOU'RE NOT LOST.

40:47.946 --> 40:49.581
YOU'RE JUST FULL OF SHIT.

40:54.586 --> 40:57.088
YOU'RE ONLY LOST
IF YOU'RE ALONE.

40:57.122 --> 41:01.927
YOU ARE SURROUNDED
BY PEOPLE WHO LOVE YOU.

41:03.194 --> 41:05.631
YOU'RE GONNA FIND YOUR WAY.

41:09.901 --> 41:11.570
NOW, GO ENJOY THE PARTY.

41:13.171 --> 41:15.974
HMM?
OH, WAIT.

41:16.007 --> 41:18.744
TSK. SHIT.

41:18.777 --> 41:19.845
[all gasp]

41:19.878 --> 41:21.747
- WOW...

41:21.780 --> 41:23.849
- OHH...

41:23.882 --> 41:26.251
- LET'S SEE!

41:26.284 --> 41:29.254
YES! OH HO HO!
LOOK!

41:29.287 --> 41:31.990
YOUR SON'S GOING TO BE
A BASEBALL PLAYER!

41:32.023 --> 41:33.692
- YEAH, WELL, IF YOU MAKE
A MAN OUT OF HIM,

41:33.725 --> 41:35.226
I'M GOING TO HOLD YOU
PERSONALLY RESPONSIBLE.

41:35.260 --> 41:40.165
- [chuckles]
- WHOO, LOOK AT YOU.

41:40.198 --> 41:41.800
- BASEBALL!
- YAY!

41:45.637 --> 41:48.273
- YOU SWING THAT BAT,
BIG BOY!

41:48.306 --> 41:51.176
- JUSTIN.
- JUSTIN!

41:51.209 --> 41:52.844
- [gasps]

42:07.659 --> 42:09.828
- OOPS.

42:09.861 --> 42:12.130
THAT WAS ONE HELL OF A FIRST
BIRTHDAY PARTY.

42:12.163 --> 42:13.899
- THANKS.

42:13.932 --> 42:15.601
- WHAT ARE YOU PLANNING TO DO
FOR HIS SECOND?

42:15.634 --> 42:17.669
- LEAVE TOWN AND STICK YOU
WITH IT.

42:17.703 --> 42:19.638
- [chuckles]
- HERE, GIVE ME A HAND.

42:19.671 --> 42:21.072
- OKAY.

42:22.373 --> 42:23.274
YOU KNOW, THIS, UH...

42:23.308 --> 42:26.211
WOULD BE THE PERFECT PLACE
FOR A WEDDING.

42:30.616 --> 42:32.984
THE WHITE SATIN BOWS
ON THE ARBOR...

42:33.018 --> 42:35.053
THE TWINKLING LIGHTS...

42:35.086 --> 42:38.089
A CHUPPAH.
ONLY NOT UNDER THE SYCAMORES.

42:38.123 --> 42:41.960
I WAS THINKING OVER
BY THE ROSE BUSHES.

42:45.330 --> 42:46.364
LINZ...

42:46.397 --> 42:50.035
- I THOUGHT WE PUT THIS
TO REST ONCE AND FOR ALL.

42:51.703 --> 42:54.072
- KENDALL MORGAN
WOKE IT UP IN ME.

42:54.105 --> 42:56.174
- WHO?

42:56.207 --> 42:58.844
- THE LITTLE GIRL WHO ASKED
IF WE WERE MARRIED.

42:58.877 --> 43:01.046
I REALIZED THAT,
SOMEDAY,

43:01.079 --> 43:05.083
OUR KID IS GOING TO ASK US
THAT VERY SAME QUESTION.

43:05.116 --> 43:07.819
AND WHEN HE DOES,
I HAVE TO SAY NO.

43:07.853 --> 43:09.287
THEN HE'D WANT
TO KNOW WHY NOT,

43:09.320 --> 43:11.356
AND THEN I'D HAVE
TO TELL HIM BECAUSE...

43:11.389 --> 43:14.325
STRAIGHT PEOPLE
WOULDN'T LET US.

43:14.359 --> 43:17.696
ONLY THAT'S NOT
THE WHOLE TRUTH.

43:17.729 --> 43:18.930
- WHICH IS?

43:18.964 --> 43:21.867
- WE WOULDN'T GIVE OURSELVES
PERMISSION.

43:26.071 --> 43:27.138
- SORRY.
- [clears throat]

43:37.282 --> 43:40.652
IF IT'S NOT TOO LATE
TO BE ROMANTIC...

43:45.123 --> 43:47.993
LINDSAY PETERSON,

43:48.026 --> 43:49.995
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

43:53.431 --> 43:55.333
- NOW YOU'RE PROPOSING
TO ME?

43:58.336 --> 44:01.306
WELL, I'M GOING
TO HAVE TO THINK IT OVER.

44:05.010 --> 44:06.111
YES!

44:06.144 --> 44:08.680
[both giggling]

44:08.714 --> 44:09.881
AAH!

44:09.915 --> 44:11.950
- [laughing]

44:11.983 --> 44:13.785
- UHH!

44:17.255 --> 44:18.790
- MMM.

44:18.824 --> 44:20.225
- [giggling]

44:20.258 --> 44:22.327
- AAAAH!

44:22.360 --> 44:25.463
[both laughing]

44:25.496 --> 44:28.099
[dishes clattering faintly]

45:00.799 --> 45:03.301
- BETTER NOW?
- MM-HMM.

45:15.246 --> 45:18.216
- YOU REALLY
FREAKED ME OUT.

45:18.249 --> 45:21.820
- WHAT, YOU?

45:21.853 --> 45:24.823
- IT WAS LIKE YOU GOT HIT
ALL OVER AGAIN.

45:27.292 --> 45:30.762
- I REMEMBERED
WALKING AWAY AND...

45:30.796 --> 45:32.998
SUDDENLY HEARING YOUR VOICE
CALL MY NAME

45:33.031 --> 45:38.003
TO WARN ME.

45:38.036 --> 45:40.238
YOU NEVER TOLD ME
ABOUT THAT.

45:41.306 --> 45:43.041
YOU TRIED TO SAVE ME.

45:45.076 --> 45:47.946
- GUESS I FORGOT.

45:55.887 --> 45:58.323
- IT'S A GOOD THING
ONE OF US REMEMBERED.

46:41.099 --> 46:43.801
I WANT YOU INSIDE ME.

46:49.941 --> 46:52.477
- ARE YOU SURE?

46:52.510 --> 46:55.113
- YEAH. JUST...

46:55.146 --> 46:57.215
TAKE IT EASY.

47:02.520 --> 47:04.522
- LIKE THE FIRST TIME?

47:37.055 --> 47:39.257
- [gasping softly]

48:02.047 --> 48:06.517
- * YOU SEE

48:06.551 --> 48:08.686
- [breathing heavily]

48:08.719 --> 48:14.525
- * ALL AROUND ME

48:14.559 --> 48:19.330
*

48:19.364 --> 48:25.270
* YOUR ARMS

48:25.303 --> 48:30.675
* SURRENDER

48:30.708 --> 48:36.381
*

48:36.414 --> 48:42.287
* YOU FEEL ME

48:42.320 --> 48:49.427
* BREATHING AS I SWOON

48:49.460 --> 48:53.164
*

48:53.198 --> 48:59.637
* SURROUND ME

48:59.670 --> 49:06.511
* WITH EVERY LIMB

49:06.544 --> 49:09.580
*

49:09.614 --> 49:16.254
* IN THE WATER

49:16.287 --> 49:21.592
* OF PARADISE

49:21.626 --> 49:26.331
*

49:26.364 --> 49:33.204
* IN THE WATER

49:33.238 --> 49:39.477
* OF PARADISE

49:39.510 --> 49:42.247
*

49:42.280 --> 49:50.155
* TILL WE'RE FREE

49:50.188 --> 49:56.227
* IN THIS PLACE

49:56.261 --> 49:59.064
*

49:59.097 --> 50:06.337
* STAY WITH ME

50:06.371 --> 50:13.078
* IN THIS PLACE

50:13.111 --> 50:14.079
*

50:14.112 --> 50:16.481
